Chord-Diagrams
==============

This program will compute the set of all unique chord diagrams
(under the dihedral group) with n chords and then computes which 
of these form a cycle.

I have not computed the exact computational complexity in terms of
n, however it is very complex. For example, at 10 chords there are 
16,411,700 UNIQUE chord diagrams and this program computes vastly
more redundant diagrams.

 For details on the mathematical question that led me to create
 this program I refer you to "Enumeration of Chord Diagrams"
 located here: http://arxiv.org/abs/math/0008209
  
 Verification for my programs validity can be found by comparing
 results of 3 and 4 vertices to the diagrams listed at the end
 of the above reference.
